Sentencas: Herein, perovskite oxide Sr2Fe1.4Co0.1Mo0.5O6-delta (SFMCo) is used as the anode of direct propane-fueled solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Co-generation of liquid chemicals and electricity over Co-Fe alloy/ perovskite anode catalyst in a propane fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In reducing operation, single-phase perovskite oxide SFMCo is transformed to Co-Fe bimetallic catalytic nanocatalysts decorated SFMCo composite nanomaterial.
Titulo: Co-generation of liquid chemicals and electricity over Co-Fe alloy/ perovskite anode catalyst in a propane fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Good electrochemical performance and outstanding stability are obtained with propane as the fuel and ambient air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Co-generation of liquid chemicals and electricity over Co-Fe alloy/ perovskite anode catalyst in a propane fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Due to the catalytic effect of the exsolved Co-Fe alloy in the SOFC system, polycyclic aromatic compounds are gathered as chemical products in the exhaust of the anode through the aromatization route.
Titulo: Co-generation of liquid chemicals and electricity over Co-Fe alloy/ perovskite anode catalyst in a propane fueled solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This novel anode system manifests the successful co-generation of electricity and high-value liquid chemicals from direct hydrocarbonfueled SOFC.
Titulo: Co-generation of liquid chemicals and electricity over Co-Fe alloy/ perovskite anode catalyst in a propane fueled solid oxide fuel cell
